{
  format: 1
  name: namespace-resolution-name-vs-contract-unspecified
  suite: static
  spec: ["#host-namespaces", "#loading"]
  tags: ["hosts"]
  note: '''
    Spec gap. The context registers an implementation of the exact required
    contract (liasse.cbor@1) but under the registration name "encoder", while
    the package requires it under the expression namespace "cbor". §16.2 says
    the requirement's local key "is the expression namespace" and the value
    "identifies the semantic contract and compatible major"; §16.4 registers
    namespaces under a name. The spec never states the matching rule between a
    requirement and the context registrations: if resolution matches the
    registration NAME against the requirement key, this load must fail as
    missing; if it matches any registration implementing the required
    CONTRACT, it must succeed (and would make two same-contract registrations
    the "ambiguous" case §16.2 mentions). Both readings are consistent with
    the text, so the outcome is not pinned.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.nsmatch@1.0.0"
    $requires: {
      cbor: "liasse.cbor@1"
    }
    $model: {
      items: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
      }
    }
  }

  hosts: {
    namespaces: {
      encoder: "liasse.cbor@1.0.0"
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: unspecified
  }
}
